# Next.js Frontend Rules

## Architecture
- App Router only — no pages/ directory
- Redux state shape is fixed: { user: { id, email, fullName, role, subscribedToId }, isAuthenticated }
- Never change authSlice state shape — it breaks all consumers
- Service functions go in src/services/api.ts matching existing patterns

## Component Rules  
- 'use client' required for any component using useState, useEffect, or event handlers
- Tailwind only for styling — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Loading states required on all data-fetching components (skeleton or spinner)
- Never use alert() — console.error() for errors, toast for user-facing messages

## TypeScript Rules
- No 'any' on new interfaces or function signatures
- Export all new interfaces from api.ts
- Match existing naming: camelCase for variables, PascalCase for components/interfaces